**Non-Alcoholic Fatty Liver Disease is characterized by the presenece of fat in the liver (>5-10%), which in not associated with other causes of steatosis, such as alcohol, viruses, drugs, toxins, autoimmune disease or iron oveload, commonly accompanied by insulin resistance.**  

